item.dc:creator: @Fr33b1e Fr33b1e
item.description:
@Fr33b1e wrote:

OK, all the int’s that was the error for the line, are in my Mining.java. Could you help me? I’m usually not so good with errors.

This is what my AddGlobalObj method is in my client.java

public void AddObject(int objectX, int objectY, int NewObjectID, int Face) {

This is the line in my Mining.java, both of them, first one is on line 171

p.AddGlobalObj(server.objectHandler.ObjectRockX[i], server.objectHandler.ObjectRockY[i], server.objectHandler.ObjectRockID[i], 0);

This one is on line 168

item.title: Int cannot be applied?
item.dc:creator: @Fir3_Flam3 Fir3 Flam3
item.description:
@Fir3_Flam3 wrote:

It means you have more ints in one thing and less in another. As it says:

(int,int,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied to (int,int,int,int)

Five then four.

To fix it, find the extra int that shouldn’t be there, then remove it.
